    "All datasets are split into three segments in a chronological order: training, validation, and test sets, with a split ratio of 7:1:2 for Traffic and Electricity.",
    "ETT dataset are split with the ratio of 6:2:2, as recommended by Informer 24 and Autoformer 25.",
    "Table 1 presents statistical information of the datasets.• ETT (Electricity Transformer Temperature) 24 including two datasets in 1-h-level (ETTh1, ETTh2) and two datasets in 15-min-level (ETTm1, ETTm2).",
    "Each dataset consists of seven electricity transformer attributes.• Traffic 30 collects data from the California.• Electricity (ECL) 30 describes the electricity consumption (Kwh) of 321 clients.",
